Two features you might have missed

recuerd0 does more than store text. Here are two capabilities worth knowing about.

1. FTS5 search operators

The API supports full SQLite FTS5 syntax. A few examples:

  # Exact phrase
  recuerd0 search '"deployment config"' --pretty

  # Boolean operators
  recuerd0 search 'rails AND deployment NOT staging' --pretty

  # Column filters
  recuerd0 search 'title:architecture' --pretty

This is especially useful when your AI tools query recuerd0 — they can write precise queries to find exactly the context they need.

2. Memory versioning

Every time you update a memory, recuerd0 saves the previous version. You can view the full history and compare changes — nothing is ever lost.

This means your AI tools can safely update shared project context. If something goes wrong, you can always roll back.

